Usage: stuff <command> [options]

Command-line dotfiles management

stuff is a tool intended to make it simple to manage dotfiles
using a repository with version control. There is a list of
commands and options below that can be called with the additional
`--help' flag for more information.

Commands:
  link                 Link local files or directories
  list                 List all of the tracked dotfiles
  unlink               Unlink local files or directories

Options:
  -h, --help           Print this help and exit
  -v, --version        Print the current version number
  -r, --root           Specify a path for another link location

